replies.body:
Hey JIIMIE,

Unfortunately we can't accept submissions for critique :(

That being said, here's some general advice:

- find your own musical voice (that will become more relevant with time), but be able to write many things;
- work harder than anyone;
- work on your musicianship;
- if you're currently studying music: school is only school. It will teach you some things about music (not nearly as much as what you learn later on), and certainly not much at all about being a professional musician. Use school for what it does best, but seek out the rest of the story as soon as you can;
- work on your production chops;
- be a good communicator (unless you plan on writing concert music exclusively);
- score reading is the answer to 90% of your musical problems (that too will become more relevant with time);
- be curious;
- I wonder what a Jedi knight would answer to that question... perhaps something not too irrelevant!  

Good luck to you!
